          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>cauliflower wedges</strong> to a separate tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, the <strong>nigella seeds </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20-25 min</p><p>After 20-25 min, add the <strong>cashew nuts</strong> to the tray and cook for 3-4 min further or until the nuts are toasted and the cauliflower is golden and crisp</p><p>Tip: Watch the cashew nuts like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
